comments: Robinson (MIA) is retreating his arm into a vertical position, and marginal contact occurs with Reid as Robinson simultaneously blocks the shot attempt.
Lowry (MIA) and McDaniels (MIN) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
Strus (MIA) legally contests Rivers' (MIN) jump shot attempt.
Lowry (MIA) and McDaniels (MIN) briefly engage and disengage as they position themselves for a potential rebound.
Lowry (MIA) is firming up over his left leg and absorbs the contact from McDaniels (MIN) to his upper body.
McDaniels (MIN) dislodges Robinson (MIA) from his rebounding position and affects his ability to pursue the ball.
Reid (MIN) brushes Robinson's (MIA) arm, causing Robinson to momentarily lose control of the ball, which he quickly recovers.
Robinson (MIA) is already in Rivers' (MIN) path and is firming up as the defenders switch.
Robinson (MIA) is moving alongside McDaniels' (MIN) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together at the same spot.
Robinson (MIA) brings his hand towards Rivers (MIN) and marginal contact occurs with Rivers' off arm/shoulder during the driving shot attempt.
Reid (MIN) and Robinson (MIA) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
Lowry (MIA) brings his hand towards Rivers' (MIN) side and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Edwards (MIN) is retreating his arm into a vertical position and makes contact with the ball as he defends Lowry's (MIA) driving shot attempt.
Possession is awarded to Miami.  Lowry (MIA) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.  Possession should have been awarded to Minnesota.

Replay review of the foul called on Lowry (MIA) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Lowry is late to the spot and does not establish a legal guarding position in Edwards' (MIN) path prior to contact.
Vincent (MIA) and Edwards (MIN) come together at the same spot and marginal lower body contact occurs during the inbound.
Lowry (MIA) cleanly deflects the ball away from Russell (MIN).
